>>cec12fdc-5d30-4e88-abf2-3e708a2c91cd
You shouldn't be using Palemoon or any other browser with Tor that's not Tor Browser (which works fine with the zite). Otherwise any zite can know your real IP by running xmlhttprequest even with Tor set to Always (I hate those labels btw, should be something like "No", "Partially" and "Enabled").
>>29058305-c99a-4502-b7bc-24268e092d9a
Yeah the problem with snowflake browsers based on old Firefox code is that javascript support changes very rapidly, and as the code for the board is 100% javascript, the de-facto standards that are Chrome and Firefox are not in sync with the browsers based in old code.

>>88b26af7-7759-44fc-bd66-e7b6dfdc94c4
If this was a ticket I'd close it as wontfix. Palemoon is not supported, period. Just switch to another browser.

>>bb1f94c4-b348-4af2-a986-8861933aa010
>I would, but I keep on having to reselect Auto-detect because Tor keeps defaulting to Manual. How do I fix that?
I don't know... Never happened to me, nor has anyone else complained about that so far.
Edit: in any case it works just fine with Firefox, it'll just be less secure than Tor Browser (but not any less secure than Palemoon).
